<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>Factorise the following expression completely:
<me>
{361 x^2-81}
</me>
</p>

<p><fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  </p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Here we use the identity:
</p>

<p>
<me>
a^2 - b^2 = (a-b)(a+b)
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Identify the two square terms.
</p>

<p>
<me>
{361 x^2-81}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
{361}x^2 = ({19}x)^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
{81} = {9}^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
So the expression has the form:
</p>

<p>
<me>
({19}x)^2 - {9}^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Apply the difference of squares identity.
</p>

<p>
<me>
({19}x)^2 - {9}^2 =
({19}x - {9})({19}x + {9})
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the factorised form is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
({19}x - {9})({19}x + {9})
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>\left(19 x-9\right) \left(19 x+9\right)</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>